<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/982>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Explore legitimate website and create duplicate] An attacker creates a website (optionally at a URL that looks similar to the original URL) that closely resembles the website that they are trying to impersonate. That website will typically have a login form for the victim to put in their authentication credentials. There can be different variations on a theme here." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Manually save copies of required web pages from legitimate site." , "Use spidering software to get copy of web pages on legitimate site." , "Create new web pages that have the legitimate site's look and feel, but contain completely new content." .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/skillRequired/66029>
        a                        capec:SkillRequired ;
        capec:isSkillRequiredOf  capec-res:CAPEC-660 ;
        capec:skillDescription   "Knowledge about code hooking." ;
        capec:skillLevel         "Medium" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/792>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Probe entry points to locate vulnerabilities] The adversary uses the entry points gathered in the \"Explore\" phase as a target list and looks for areas where user input is used to access resources on the target host. The adversary attempts different encodings of slash characters to bypass input filters." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Try both backslash and forward slash characters" , "Try different encodings for slash characters such as %5C" .

