<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/6953>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Exploit victims] The adversary's malicious code is incorporated into applications that directly reference the initial repository, which further allows the adversary to conduct additional attacks." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/6763>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Experiment with NoSQL Injection vulnerabilities] After determining that a given input is vulnerable to NoSQL Injection, hypothesize what the underlying query looks like. Iteratively try to add logic to the query to extract information from the database, modify/delete information in the database, or execute commands on the server." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Iteratively add logic to the NoSQL query and use detailed error messages from the server to debug the query." , "Use public resources such as OWASP's \"Testing for NoSQL Injection\" [REF-668] or Null Sweep's \"NoSQL Injection Cheatsheet\" [REF-669] and try different approaches for adding logic to NoSQL queries." , "Attempt an HTTP Parameter Pollution attack to replace language-specific keywords, such as \"where\" within PHP [CAPEC-460]." .

