<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/881>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "1" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Identify inputs for OS commands] The attacker determines user controllable input that gets passed as part of a command to the underlying operating system." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "TCP/IP Fingerprinting. The attacker uses various software to make connections or partial connections and observe idiosyncratic responses from the operating system. Using those responses, they attempt to guess the actual operating system." , "Port mapping. Identify ports that the system is listening on, and attempt to identify inputs and protocol types on those ports." , "Induce errors to find informative error messages" .

