<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/691>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "1" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Find programs with elevated priveleges] The adversary probes for programs running with elevated privileges." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Look for programs that write to the system directories or registry keys (such as HKLM, which stores a number of critical Windows environment variables). These programs are typically running with elevated privileges and have usually not been designed with security in mind. Such programs are excellent exploit targets because they yield lots of power when they break." .

