<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/844>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "4" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Manipulate the data in the XML database] The attacker crafts and injects an XQuery payload which is acted on by an XQL query leading to modification of application data." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Leveraging one of the vulnerable inputs identified during the Experiment phase, inject malicious XQuery payload.. The payload tries to insert or replace data in the XML database." .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/1971>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "1" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Survey the target] An adversary determines the input data stream that is being processed by a data parser that supports using subsitituion on the victim's side." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Use an automated tool to record all instances of URLs to process requests." , "Use a browser to manually explore the website and analyze how the application processes requests." .

