<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/802>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Probe entry points to locate vulnerabilities] The attacker uses the entry points gathered in the \"Explore\" phase as a target list and injects various UTF-8 encoded payloads to determine if an entry point actually represents a vulnerability with insufficient validation logic and to characterize the extent to which the vulnerability can be exploited." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Try to use UTF-8 encoding of content in HTML in order to bypass validation routines." , "Try to use UTF-8 encoding of content in Scripts in order to bypass validation routines." , "Try to use UTF-8 encoding of content in CSS in order to bypass validation routines." .

