<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/1702>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Increase the accuracy of server fingerprinting of Web servers] Attacker usually needs to send several different commands to accurately identify the web server. Attacker can also use automated tools to send requests to the server. The responses of the server may be different in terms of protocol behavior." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Send bad requests or requests of nonexistent pages to the server." , "Observe the ordering of the several HTTP response headers. The ordering of the header of each server may have unique identities." , "Attacker takes existing automated tools to recognize the type and the version of the web server in use." .

