<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/1832>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Identify Vulnerable Parameters] Once the adversary has identified a web-mail server, they identify any vulnerable parameters by altering their values in requests. The adversary knows that the parameter is vulnerable if the web-mail server returns an error of any sort. Ideally, the adversary is looking for a descriptive error message." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Add non standard special characters (i.e.: \\, ', \", @, #, !, |) to a parameter being used by the web-mail server and observe the response." , "Assign a null value to a parameter being used by the web-mail server and observe the response." , "Assign a random value to a parameter being used by the web-mail server and observe the response." , "Eliminate a parameter being used by the web-mail server and observe the response." , "Add additional values to a parameter being used by the web-mail server and observe the response." .

