<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/4623>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Infer information from the response time] After obtaining reponse times to various requests, the adversary will compare these times and infer potentially sensitive information. An example of this could be asking a service to retrieve information and random usernames. If one request took longer to process, it is likely that a user with that username exists, which could be useful knowledge to an adversary." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Compare timing of different requests to infer potentially sensitive information about a target service" .

