<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/1633>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Optional: Explore legitimate website and create duplicate] An adversary creates a website (optionally at a URL that looks similar to the original URL) that closely resembles the website that they are trying to impersonate. That website will typically have a login form for the victim to put in their authentication credentials. There can be different variations on a theme here." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Manually save copies of required web pages from legitimate site." , "Use spidering software to get copy of web pages on legitimate site." , "Create new web pages that have the legitimate site's look at feel, but contain completely new content." .

