<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/1981>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "1" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Survey the application for user-controllable inputs as URL parameters] Using a browser or an automated tool, an adversary follows all public links and actions on a web site. They record all the links, the forms, the resources accessed and all other potential entry-points for the web application, looking for URLs which use parameters." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Use a proxy tool to record all links visited during a manual traversal of the web application." , "Use a spidering tool to follow and record all links and analyze the web pages to find entry points. Make note of any links that include parameters in the URL." , "Use a browser to manually explore the website and analyze how it is constructed. Many browsers' plugins are available to facilitate the analysis or automate the discovery." .

