<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/664>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "4" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Exploit SQL Injection vulnerability] After refining and adding various logic to SQL queries, craft and execute the underlying SQL query that will be used to attack the target system. The goal is to reveal, modify, and/or delete database data, using the knowledge obtained in the previous step. This could entail crafting and executing multiple SQL queries if a denial of service attack is the intent." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Craft and Execute underlying SQL query" .

