<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/284>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "4" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Craft exploit payloads] Put specially crafted input into the system that leverages the weakness identified through fuzzing and allows to achieve the goals of the attacker. Fuzzers often reveal ways to slip through the input validation filters and introduce unwanted data into the system." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Embed higher level attack commands in the payload. (e.g., SQL, PHP, server-side includes, etc.)" , "Identify and embed shell code for the target system." , "Induce denial of service by exploiting resource leaks or bad error handling." .

