<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/2611>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "1" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Observe communication and inputs] The fuzzing adversary observes the target system looking for inputs and communications between modules, subsystems, or systems." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Monitor API execution. Using a tool such as ktrace, strace, APISpy, or another debugging tool, the adversary observes the system calls and API calls that are made by the target system, and the nature of their parameters." , "Network sniffing. Using a network sniffer such as wireshark, the adversary observes communications into and out of the target system." , "Observe inputs using web inspection tools (OWASP's WebScarab, Paros, TamperData, TamperIE, etc.)" .

