<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/905>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "5" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Receive encrypted challenge] The server treats the intial client challenge in connection two as an arbitrary client challenge and responds by encrypting C with the pre-shared key. The server also sends a new challenge. The adversary ignores the server challenge and stores the encrypted version of C. The second connection is either terminated or left to expire by the adversary as it is no longer needed." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" .

