<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/1833>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Determine Level of Injection] After identifying all vulnerable parameters, the adversary determines what level of injection is possible." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Evaluate error messages to determine what IMAP/SMTP command is being executed for the vulnerable parameter. Sometimes the actually query will be placed in the error message." , "If there aren't descriptive error messages, the adversary will analyze the affected functionality to deduce the possible commands that could be being used by the mail-server." .

