        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "4" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Determine database type] Determines the type of the database, such as MS SQL Server or Oracle or MySQL, using logical conditions as part of the injected queries" ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Try injecting a string containing 0x313D31 (this evaluates to 1=1 in MySQL only)" , "Try injecting a string containing char(0x31)=char(0x31) (this evaluates to 1=1 in SQL Server only)" , "Inject other database-specific commands into input fields susceptible to SQL Injection. The adversary can determine the type of database that is running by checking whether the query executed successfully or not (i.e. whether the adversary received a normal response from the server or not)." .

