<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/5004>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "4" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Inject malicious code] Once the victim runs the malicious application and views the targeted web page in the WebView component, the malicious application will inject malicious JavaScript code into the web application. This is done by using WebView's loadURL() API, which can inject arbitrary JavaScript code into pages loaded by the WebView component with the same privileges. This is often done by adding a script tag to the document body with a src destination to a remote location that serves malicious JavaScript code." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Steal cookie information from the victim." , "Execute operations on the targeted web page on behalf of an authenticated user." , "Add in extra fields to the DOM in an attempt to get a user to divulge sensitive information." .

