<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/113>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[File misclassification sniping] Understanding how certain file types are processed by web servers, an attacker crafts varying file payloads and modifies their file extension or MIME type to be that of the targeted type to see if the web server is vulnerable to misclassification of that type." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Craft a malicious file payload, modify file extension to the targeted file type and submit it to the web server." , "Craft a malicious file payload, modify its associated MIME type to the targeted file type and submit it to the web server." .

