<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/6562>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Explore legitimate website and create duplicate] An adversary optionally creates a website (optionally at a URL that looks similar to the original URL) that closely resembles the organization's website that they are trying to impersonate. That website will contain a telephone number for the victim to call to assist them with their issue and initiate the attack. If the adversary leverages cold-calling for this attack, this step is skipped." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Manually save copies of required web pages from legitimate site." , "Use spidering software to get copy of web pages on legitimate site." , "Create new web pages that have the legitimate site's look and feel, but contain completely new content." .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/6372>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Target users of the application] An adversary will target users of the application in order to obtain the information in their clipboard on a periodic basic" ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Install malware on a user's system designed to log clipboard contents periodically" , "Get the user to click on a malicious link that will bring them to an application to log the contents of the clipboard" .

