<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/1093>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Perform SQL Injection through the generated data access layer] An attacker proceeds to exploit a weakness in the generated data access methods that does not properly separate control plane from the data plan, or potentially a particular way in which developer might have misused the generated code, to modify the structure of the executed SQL queries and/or inject entirely new SQL queries." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "An attacker uses normal SQL injection techniques and adjusts them to reflect the type of data access layer generation framework used by the application." .

