<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/5603>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Attempt authentication] Try each credential until the target grants access." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Manually or automatically enter each credential through the target's interface." .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/893>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "When the victim requests the URL for the site, the poisoned records direct the victim to the attackers' system rather than the original one." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/5223>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Substitute Components in the Supply Chain] Using the vulnerability in the supply chain of the system discovered in the explore phase, the adversary substitutes the malicious component for the targeted component. This results in the adversary gaining unintended access to systems once they reach the victim and can lead to a variety of follow up attacks." , "[Test a Malicious Component Replacement] Before performing the attack in the wild, an adversary will test the attack on a system they have procured to ensure that the desired outcome will be achieved." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" , "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Design a malicious hardware component that will perform the same functionality as the target component, but also contains additional functionality." , "Obtain already designed malicious components that just need to be placed into the system." .

