<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/661>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "1" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Survey application] The attacker first takes an inventory of the functionality exposed by the application." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Spider web sites for all available links" , "Sniff network communications with application using a utility such as WireShark." .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/471>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "1" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Identify target application] The adversary identifies a target application or program to perform the buffer overflow on. Adversaries often look for applications that accept user input and that perform manual memory management." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" .

