        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Perform SQL injection." , "Perform command injection." , "Gain access to sensitive files." , "Perform XSS attacks." .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/244>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "4" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Abuse the system through filter failure] An attacker writes a script to consistently induce the filter failure." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Malicious code execution. An attacker introduces a malicious payload and executes arbitrary code on the target system." , "DoS through filter failure. The attacker causes the system to crash or stay down because of its failure to filter properly." , "An attacker can use the filter failure to introduce malicious data into the system and leverage a subsequent SQL injection, Cross Site Scripting, Command Injection or similar weakness if it exists." .

