<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/522>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Probe entry points to locate vulnerabilities] The adversary uses the entry points gathered in the \"Explore\" phase as a target list and injects postfix null byte(s) to observe how the application handles them as input. The adversary is looking for areas where user input is placed in the middle of a string, and the null byte causes the application to stop processing the string at the end of the user input." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Try different encodings for null such as \\0 or %00" .

