<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/1362>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Determine user-controllable input susceptible to LDAP injection] For each user-controllable input that the attacker suspects is vulnerable to LDAP injection, attempt to inject characters that have special meaning in LDAP (such as a single quote character, etc.). The goal is to create a LDAP query with an invalid syntax" ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Experiment" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Use a web application debugging tool such as Tamper Data, TamperIE, WebScarab,etc. to modify HTTP POST parameters, hidden fields, non-freeform fields, or other HTTP header." , "Use web browser to inject input through text fields or through HTTP GET parameters" , "Use modified client (modified by reverse engineering) to inject input." .

