<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/592>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "2" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Characterize IDs] The attacker studies the characteristics of the session ID (size, format, etc.). As a results the attacker finds that legitimate session IDs are predictable." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Explore" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Pattern tests. The attacker looks for patterns (odd/even, repetition, multiples, or other arithmetic relationships) between IDs" , "Cryptanalysis. The attacker uses cryptanalysis to determine if the session IDs contain any cryptographic protections." , "Comparison against time. The attacker plots or compares the issued IDs to the time they were issued to check for correlation." .

