<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/76>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "6" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "[Exploit SQL Injection vulnerability] Use the information obtained in the previous steps to successfully inject the database in order to bypass checks or modify, add, retrieve or delete data from the database" ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" ;
        capec:attackStepTechnique    "Use information about how to inject commands into SQL queries as well as information about the database schema to execute attacks such as dropping tables, inserting records, etc." .

<http://w3id.org/sepses/resource/capec/ExecutionFlow/263>
        a                            capec:AttackStep ;
        capec:attackStep             "3" ;
        capec:attackStepDescription  "The resource is modified/checked concurrently by multiple processes. By using one of the processes, the adversary is able to modify the value just before it is consumed by a different process. A race condition occurs and is exploited by the adversary to abuse the target host." ;
        capec:attackStepPhase        "Exploit" .

capec-res:CAPEC-585  a                 capec:CAPEC ;
        dct:description                "In this attack pattern, an adversary influences a target's web-hosting company to disable a target domain. The goal is to prevent access to the targeted service provided by that domain. It usually occurs as the result of civil or criminal legal interventions." ;
